# Cline Rules — Automated Vendor Assessment Framework (PoC)

## Project Overview

This is a full-stack PoC for Carlsberg to automate AI startup vendor vetting and risk scoring across 8 compliance dimensions. It reduces time-to-onboard and produces structured, actionable reports.

---

## Tech Stack

### Backend

- **Language:** Python 3.11+
- **Framework:** FastAPI (async-native, not Django)
- **ORM:** SQLAlchemy (async) with Alembic for migrations
- **Validation:** Pydantic v2 schemas
- **PDF Generation:** WeasyPrint (pure Python, no Chromium/Puppeteer)
- **LLM:** OpenRouter API (free-tier models: `meta-llama/llama-3-8b-instruct:free`, Mistral, Gemma) — NOT local Ollama
- **Auth:** JWT (HS256), short-lived access token (15 min) + refresh token (7 days)
- **Email:** Mailhog SMTP (PoC only, not production SMTP)

### Frontend

- **Framework:** React 18 + Vite + TypeScript
- **State Management:** React Query (server state), no Redux
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod (validation)
- **UI Components:** shadcn/ui (Tailwind-based)
- **Charts:** Recharts

### Infrastructure

- **Database:** PostgreSQL 16 (Docker volume)
- **Container Orchestration:** Docker Compose
- **Reverse Proxy:** Nginx (port 80 → routes `/` to React port 3000, `/api/*` to FastAPI port 8000)
- **Dev Email:** Mailhog (SMTP port 1025, UI port 8025)

---

## Project Structure Conventions

```
vendor-assessment-poc/
├── backend/
│   └── app/
│       ├── api/           # Route handlers ONLY (thin controllers)
│       ├── services/      # Business logic (vendor, scoring, report, task, notify)
│       ├── scoring/       # One scorer per dimension + base class
│       ├── models/        # SQLAlchemy ORM models
│       ├── schemas/       # Pydantic request/response schemas
│       └── core/          # Config, database engine, security helpers
├── frontend/
│   └── src/
│       ├── pages/         # One file per page/route
│       ├── components/    # Reusable UI components
│       └── api/           # API client functions (React Query hooks)
├── nginx/
│   └── nginx.conf
└── docs/                  # Architecture and phase documentation
```

### Backend Conventions

- Route handlers in `api/` should be thin — delegate all logic to `services/`
- Each SQLAlchemy model lives in `models/<entity>.py`
- Each Pydantic schema lives in `schemas/<entity>.py`
- Use async SQLAlchemy sessions throughout
- All config from environment variables via `core/config.py` (Settings class with pydantic-settings)
- **No secrets or hardcoded credentials in source code**

### Frontend Conventions

- Pages live in `src/pages/`, components in `src/components/`
- API calls are wrapped in React Query hooks inside `src/api/`
- Use shadcn/ui components first before writing custom ones
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types

---

## The 8 Assessment Dimensions

| #   | Dimension                      | Scorer File             | Owner            |
| --- | ------------------------------ | ----------------------- | ---------------- |
| 1   | Security, Privacy & Compliance | `security_scorer.py`    | IT Security      |
| 2   | Vendor Viability & Continuity  | `viability_scorer.py`   | Procurement      |
| 3   | Integration & Data Integrity   | `integration_scorer.py` | IT / Engineering |
| 4   | Legal & IP                     | `legal_scorer.py`       | Legal            |
| 5   | Cost & Commercials             | `commercial_scorer.py`  | Procurement      |
| 6   | Operations & Change Management | `operations_scorer.py`  | Procurement / IT |
| 7   | Global Scalability             | `scalability_scorer.py` | IT / Engineering |
| 8   | Product Maturity & Delivery    | `maturity_scorer.py`    | AI Innovation    |

Each dimension is scored **0–100** and flagged 🟢 Green (≥70) / 🟡 Amber (40–69) / 🔴 Red (<40).

---

## Scoring Engine Architecture

### Scorer Pattern

All scorers extend `base_scorer.py` (`BaseScorer` abstract class). Each scorer implements:

1. **Rules-based scoring** — deterministic checks on structured intake form fields
2. **LLM-assisted scoring** — uploaded documents sent to OpenRouter with dimension-specific prompts

### Scoring Formula

```
Final Dimension Score = 0.6 × RulesScore + 0.4 × LLMScore
```

### LLM Integration

- Use OpenRouter API at `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1`
- Default model: `meta-llama/llama-3-8b-instruct:free`
- Document text is extracted, chunked if needed, then prompted with structured criteria
- Parse LLM response to extract numeric sub-score + reasoning text

---

## Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

| Table              | Purpose                                                       |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `vendors`          | Company info, submitted docs, onboarding status               |
| `assessments`      | One per vendor — tracks run state + timestamps                |
| `dimension_scores` | One row per dimension per assessment (score, flags, evidence) |
| `reports`          | Generated report metadata + PDF file path                     |
| `tasks`            | Action items: title, description, dept, assignee, status      |
| `users`            | Assessor accounts with roles                                  |
| `enrichment_cache` | Cached external API results (TTL 7 days)                      |

---

## RBAC Roles

| Role            | Access                                           |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `admin`         | Full access                                      |
| `procurement`   | Vendor intake, commercial dimension, tasks       |
| `it_security`   | Security dimension, integration dimension, tasks |
| `legal`         | Legal/IP dimension, tasks                        |
| `ai_innovation` | Product maturity dimension, read-only            |

---

## External APIs (Free Tier)

| API             | Purpose                        | Base URL                                           |
| --------------- | ------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------- |
| NVD (NIST)      | CVE vulnerabilities            | `https://services.nvd.nist.gov/rest/json/cves/2.0` |
| Companies House | UK company registration data   | `https://api.company-information.service.gov.uk`   |
| OpenCorporates  | International company registry | `https://api.opencorporates.com`                   |
| OpenRouter      | LLM inference                  | `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1`                     |

- Cache all external API results in `enrichment_cache` table with 7-day TTL to avoid hammering free-tier limits.

