---

## Key Design Decisions (Do Not Change Without Discussion)

| Decision                     | Rationale                                                    |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| FastAPI over Django          | Async-native, faster to prototype, excellent OpenAPI docs    |
| PostgreSQL over SQLite       | Concurrent writes, JSON column support, production-viable    |
| OpenRouter over local Ollama | Reliable free-tier models without GPU requirements           |
| Mailhog over real SMTP       | Zero config, zero cost, PoC-appropriate                      |
| WeasyPrint over Puppeteer    | Pure Python, simpler Docker build, no Chromium dependency    |
| React + shadcn/ui            | Fast enterprise-looking UI without a designer                |
| React Query over Redux       | Server state management is sufficient; avoids Redux overhead |

---

## Environment Variables

- All configuration via `.env` (copied from `.env.example`)
- Key variables: `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `JWT_SECRET`
- Never hardcode secrets or commit `.env` to version control
- Use `core/config.py` (pydantic-settings `BaseSettings`) to load and validate env vars

